modules.description: Converts a JSON-formatted backtrace string into a structured backtrace value. Works with string inputs representing the source name and JSON data. Useful for parsing and handling backtraces stored or transmitted in JSON format.

This module captures, manipulates, and prints backtraces for debugging exceptions. It supports stashing and restoring backtraces during exception handling, associating backtraces with exceptions, and converting between JSON and structured backtrace formats. Use cases include preserving backtraces when re-raising exceptions, merging backtraces from multiple sources, and logging human-readable backtraces.
